Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
uiFind(25.10)                                                    uiFind(25.10)

Name
       uiFind  -  Enables  you  to  retrieve an element's name by specifying a
       property-value combination

Syntax
       uiFind

       [-help]

       [<name>]

       [<property> {<value>}]

       Enables you to retrieve an element's name  by  specifying  a  property-
       value combination.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each uiFind parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man uiFind

       <name> Specifies  the  name  of the parent element to define the search
              scope. If multiple elements are found with the same <name>,  the
              first matched element is searched. If <name> is not specified, a
              global search is performed.

       <property>{<value>}
              Specifies  the property-value combination that should be used as
              the search criteria for finding an element. In addition  to  all
              the properties listed in the uiAdd command, -type <type> is also
              supported.

              To  see  the  list of properties supported by the uiAdd command,
              see uiAdd.

Examples
              * The following command returns the names of all  the  menus  in
                the main window:

                uiFind main -type menu

                The software returns the following:

                file  view  edit  partition  fplan power place eco clock route
                timing verify pvs tools windows flow help

              * The following command returns the names of detachable submenus
                (that is, with menu_separate setting as true) in the View menu
                that are detachable main window:

                uiFind view -menu_separate true

                The software returns the following with default settings:

                view.zoom view.pan view.hilite view.clear_hilite

              * The following command returns the name of the  element  before
                the Help menu in the main window:

                uiFind -before help

                The software returns the following:

                flow

              * The  following  command returns the name of the element with a
                label "CCOpt Clock Tree Debugger..." on the menu in  the  main
                window:

                uiFind -label "CCOpt Clock Tree Debugger..."

                The software returns the following:

                _CCOpt_Clock_Tree_Debugger...

                You  can  then get any property of the element by using uiGet.
                For example:

                uiGet _CCOpt_Clock_Tree_Debugger... -command

                The software returns the following:

                ctdMainWin::createSetting

                Here, ctdMainWin::createSetting is the command that is invoked
                when the menu item labeled CCOpt  Clock  Tree  Debugger...  is
                clicked.

              * The following command returns all movable toolbars in the main
                window:

                uiFind -movable true

                The software returns the following:

                tbFile  tbEdit  tbView tbTools tbReport tbToolBox we main.lay-
                out.selectbar

